node.text:
Minimalistic beach residence ✨ #archoskar
The 'McAnally Residence'.
Designed by MADDOCK Buildings & Interiors (@gavinmaddockdesignstudio).
Located in Sunshine Beach, Australia.
Photos by Scott Burrows Photographer (@scottburrowsphotographer).
Description by MADDOCK Buildings & Interiors.
.
"Architecture is the learned game, correct and magnificent, of forms assembled in the light." — Le Corbusier. #architectureoskar
.
The stylishly designed house rises out of the sand dune, overlooking the ocean at Sunshine Beach, on the east coast of Australia, approximately 120km north of Brisbane. The structure is terraced up the dune over three levels, accommodating three guest suites on the lower level and the master suite on the upper level. The central level occupies the main living area of the dwelling, with direct access to two terraces and the cantilevered swimming pool.
.
#sunshine #beach #minimalistic #australia

node.text:
World largest monastery library 📚 #archoskar
The 'Admont Abbey Library' (70,000 books).
Designed by Joseph Hueber (1776).
Located in Admont, Austria.
Video by Madeline (@madelinestraveling).
Song by Duomo, 'Wildest Dreams'.
Description by Stift Admont.
.
"If you have a garden and a library, you have everything you need." — Marcus Tullius Cicero. #architectureoskar
.
The world-famous Admont library is located in the east wing of the abbey building. It is 70 metres long, 14 metres wide and 11 metres high (reaching a maximum height of 12.7 metres in the central cupola), making this room the largest monastic library in the world. In the past, this hall was sometimes referred to as the 'eighth Wonder of the World'. The interplay of its vast dimensions, its architectural structure, its book holdings and artistic decoration has taken away the breath of visitors since its creation.
.
#library #abbey #books #austria

node.text:
Lunch in Venice ✨ #archoskar
The 'St. Regis Venice' (@stregisvenice, 5-star hotel).
Designed by Marriott Bonvoy (@marriottbonvoy).
Located in Venice, Italy.
Video by Alex (@alexpreview).
Song by Dean Martin, 'Buona Sera'.
Description by Marriott Bonvoy.
.
"Every block of stone has a statue inside it and it is the task of the sculptor to discover it." — Michelangelo. #architectureoskar
.
Avant-garde in outlook and design, The St. Regis Venice merges striking, modern interiors with its historic provenance as the best address in the city. Flanked by the Grand Canal with views across iconic landmarks, the hotel has stood in this privileged position for over a century and a half. Stylish design, intelligent technology and St. Regis Butlers cultivate an environment of impeccable comfort in 130 guestrooms and 39 suites, a selection of which graced with private terrace.
.
#lunch #venice #italy #michelangelo

node.text:
Boutique Mexican hotel ✨ #archoskar
The 'Casona Sforza' (@casonasforza).
Designed by Alberto Kalach_TAX (@kalach_tax, 2020).
Located in Puerto Escondido, Oaxaca, Mexico.
Photos by Alex Krotkov (@alex.krotkov).
Description by Alberto Kalach_TAX.
.
"To design is to communicate clearly by whatever means you can control or master." — Milton Glaser. #architectureoskar
.
'Casona Sforza' develops from the idea of being aware of the environment, the contemplation and respect for the environment that is described as a "(…) place on the Oaxacan coast –where the delta of the Colotepec river converges with the sea– the sabines, the mangroves, the tulles and the oaks embrace this exuberant refuge to privilege a reunion with the essential and natural beauty without artifice."
.
#boutique #hotel #mexico #pool

node.text:
Minimalistic rooftop residence 🤍 #archoskar
The 'ÀTIC BLANC'.
Designed by Fran Silvestre Arquitectos (@fransilvestrearquitectos).
Located in Valencia, Spain.
Photos by Diego Opazo (@diegoopazofotografo).
Description by Fran Silvestre Arquitectos.
.
"Rooftops are like another city that exists above the one we know." — Álvaro Siza Vieira. #architectureoskar
.
This space opens onto different terraces on both sides, favoring natural cross ventilation. The night area is located on the other side of the access. The axiality of the proposal appears in all of the rooms, and is enhanced by the arrangement of different elements, such as the linear lights on the ceiling, or the fixed furniture. The terrace is understood as a kind of atrium open to the sky, seeking the feeling of being in an isolated building from which to contemplate the city of Valencia.
.
#rooftop #bright #minimalistic #valencia
